        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:58PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arden, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mertzon, Arden, Sherwood, and Us-67 Near The Irion-
Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
